+**Bug: malformed evaluate `status="error"` left the trial in starting.**
+Correct. Per 03-roles.md §4.4, `status="error"` always drives the trial
+to `error` — the worker declared trial failure, independent of whether
+the payload fields are valid. Refactored `_reject_evaluate`:
+
+- Trial-side transition is now a function of `submission.status`, not
+  of the orchestrator's reject `reason`.
+- `status="error"` → trial transitions to `error`, `completed_at` is
+  written, `trial.errored` emitted. If `reason=="validation_error"`,
+  the invalid `metrics`/`artifacts_uri` are dropped; the trial-side
+  transition itself still happens.
+- `status="eval_error"` → trial stays in `starting` (§4.4 evaluator-
+  side failure).
+- `status="success"` (only reachable via validation_error on a
+  malformed success) → trial stays in `starting` (orchestrator never
+  observed a valid success verdict).
+
+The test that previously encoded the wrong behavior
+(`test_error_submission_with_bad_metrics_routed_to_validation_error`)
+now asserts the correct post-condition: `trial.status=="error"`,
+`metrics=None` (dropped), `completed_at` set, `trial.errored` in the
+log.
+
+**Nit: stale driver docstring.** Updated to reference
+`validate_terminal` rather than `validate_acceptance` and to call out
+the validation-error path for `status="error"` submissions too.
+
